SIMPLE: instability
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instability
<hw>In`sta*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Instabilities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>instabilitas</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>instabilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or condition of being unstable; lack of
stability, firmness, or steadiness; liability to give way or to fail;
insecurity; precariousness; <as>as, the <ex>instability</ex> of a
building</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lack of determination of fixedness; inconstancy;
fickleness; mutability; changeableness; <as>as, <ex>instability</ex> of
character, temper, custom, etc.</as></def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Inconstancy; fickleness; changeableness;
wavering; unsteadiness; unstableness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instable</ent>⟦br⟧
